      "snowpackStructure": {
        "comment": "40 to 80 cm of snow, and even more in some localities, fell in the last few days. Up to intermediate altitudes rain has fallen. <br/> <br/> Some snow will fall. The wind will be strong for a temporary period. <br/> <br/> The snowpack will be prone to triggering. Large quantities of fresh snow and the wind-drifted snow are bonding only slowly with the old snowpack. The various wind slabs have bonded insufficiently with each other and the old snowpack. <br/> Avalanche prone weak layers exist in the bottom section of the snowpack on west, north and east facing slopes. <br/> <br/> The rain gave rise to softening of the snowpack at low and intermediate altitudes."
      },
